    "abhinav": {
      "author": "Sri Abhinav Gupta",
      "et":
          "3.40 Indriyani etc.  In the beginning, it stands on the sense organs at work.  For example, when an enemy is sighted with eyes, he generates wrath about himself at the very place of the perceiver's  sense-organ,  then in the mind i.e., fancy,  then in the intellect, i.e., resolve; and producing delusion in this way, it destroys knowledge.\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n [The Lord]  speaks of the means for avoiding this foe as :",
      "sc":
          "।।3.40।।इन्द्रियाणीति।  आदाविन्द्रियेषु  व्यापृतेषु  सत्सु तिष्ठति।  यथा चक्षुषा शत्रुः दृष्टः इन्द्रियप्रदेशेएव क्रोधमात्मनो जनयति।  ततो मनसि संकल्पे ततो बुद्धौ निश्चये एतद्द्वारेण मोहं जनयन् ज्ञानंनाशयति।"
    },
